Holy Knight of Truth</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch!</span><br>  Posts: 801<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/13/01 10:33:37 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/fenye.jpg width=92 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &lt;-- Ignorant Paranoia Sets In</span><hr size=1> Well, it's not really like that for the planes.  You see, all the members of the really big guilds that matter on server have either all their planar already, or almost all of it.<br>
<br>
They've been raiding hate &amp; fear since before Kunark.  They've after the Trak's, the VS's.  Only reason for most of them to go to hate/fear would be for their epic.  (Ie: Nillon needs the hand of Maestro)<br>
<br>
More of Small guild 1 signs up for a raid on Monday. Small guild 1 takes themselves, &amp; Small guild 3.  Small guild 2 signs up Tues.  They take 2 &amp; 4.  Small guild 3 signs up Wed.  They take 1 &amp; 3.  Big guild signs up Thurs, they take themselves &amp; a few others.<br>
<br>
This happens a bit, but it generally doesn't matter, as you can have 1 raid a day.  It's not like VS, where this kind of stuff leads to a 9 month rotation. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="315" height="200"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminutemanaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minute Manaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/13/01 11:06:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &lt;-- Ignorant Paranoia Sets In</span><hr size=1> So its possible but it just doesn't happen?<br>
<br>
That kinda makes sense.  I mean, with all the things to raid, and there being only X numbers of people on the server.  Even if all of them at once wanted to go, at 40 people per raid, per night, that gives everyone a pretty decent chance I guess.<br>
<br>
Ok, noted, and thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 267<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/14/01 12:44:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &lt;-- Ignorant Paranoia Sets In</span><hr size=1> I'm guessing from the two posts you've made that you are looking to host a hate raid.   All you have to do as an Indy is sign up before anyone else 14 days in advance without posting before midnight board time.  If you are the first then you get the plane for that day.  But you can't have two dates in the same plane at any time.  Meaning you can't take a 2nd date until after the 1st date is passed.<br>
<br>
Then just post a sign up list.  As proven by Belieal, it doesn't matter who you are or what guild you are in or arent in or what kind of person you are... you will always get sign ups.   Now as to the quality of those sign ups is a different matter.  Or do strictly invite only if you wish. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1295<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/14/01 6:29:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &lt;-- Ignorant Paranoia Sets In</span><hr size=1> Adun..it doesn't happen all that often when guilds get together and combine raids where they all have their raids in the two week period.  Let's not mislead people.   It happens but it is far from an epidemic....sheesh you'd think that the small guilds are all in cahoots.  They aren't.  Most raids are a myriad of whoever signs up and who ever is well known to be a good raider more so than their damn tag.  Does everything have to be a conspiracy?  Sheesh.<br>
<br>
Saph <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminutemanaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minute Manaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/14/01 6:35:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &lt;-- Ignorant Paranoia Sets In</span><hr size=1> Twiggie,<br>
<br>
Heh... actually no friend, you won't see me hosting any raids any time in the near future.  I was reading through some of these raid discussion posts though.  Some of the issues that are being and have been dealt with.  Thats what provoked my curosity.<br>
<br>
I have been contemplating doing a few raids though.  I have a few friends who consistantly ask me to go to the planes with them.  I have never had the desire to do so, but my concern is that if I do go to assist a friend in the area, I don't want to be completely unprepared.  That of course is never a good situation.  And from what little experience in the planes I have had, I've found it to be quite a different situation then the normal 6 man groups I run.<br>
<br>
So yes my attention is poised a bit.  Hope you don't mind answering a few 'newbie' questions along the way.  =)<br>
<br>
Minute Manaslayer<br>
